Feature: validating Place API's

@AddPlace
Scenario Outline: Verify if place is being successfully added using ADD Place API

Given Add Place PayLoad using <name> <address> and <language>
When user calls "AddPlaceAPI" using "POST" Http request
Then the API call should be success with status code 200
And "status" in response body is "OK"
And "scope" in response body is "APP"
And verify placeid generated by calling "GetPlaceAPI" using "GET" http request
 

Examples:
|	name	|	address	|	language	|
|	swathi1	|	xyz	|	telugu	|
|	shreyanvi1	|	tyy	|	kannada	|
|	sarada1	|	redf	|	tamil	|


@DeletePlace
Scenario: Verify delete Place API

Given Placeid which needs to be deleted
When user calls "DeletePlaceAPI" using "DELETE" Http request
Then the API call should be success with status code 200
And "status" in response body is "OK"


